The proclamation by the Tana Delta elders gives the campaign against FGM a boost. 

Men-End-FGM Coordinator Tony Mwebia, said men are key to ending the practice as they are the major decision-makers. 

"In pastoralist communities especially, men provide everything; they are the key decision-makers, they even give money to pay the surgeons. If we can have the men support the quest to end the practice, then we will win by 2022," he said. 

FGM activist Sadiya Hussein said men are pivotal in ending the practice as they are the ones who have been pushing for circumcised women for wives. 

Ms Sadiya advised the government to air the video in public places among the concerned communities. 

